WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:01.936 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:01.936 --> 00:00:04.360 align:middle line:90%


00:00:04.360 --> 00:00:05.760 align:middle line:84%
HARRY (VOICEOVER):
New York City,

00:00:05.760 --> 00:00:09.310 align:middle line:90%
the only home I've ever known.

00:00:09.310 --> 00:00:11.100 align:middle line:84%
I used to feel small
and insignificant

00:00:11.100 --> 00:00:17.100 align:middle line:84%
among the skyscrapers,
but not anymore.

00:00:17.100 --> 00:00:19.650 align:middle line:84%
Today, when I stop at
my favorite storefront

00:00:19.650 --> 00:00:21.870 align:middle line:84%
and check my reflection
in the mirror,

00:00:21.870 --> 00:00:23.615 align:middle line:90%
it's clear I've changed.

00:00:23.615 --> 00:00:27.500 align:middle line:90%


00:00:27.500 --> 00:00:30.380 align:middle line:90%
That's me, Harry.

00:00:30.380 --> 00:00:33.840 align:middle line:84%
And as you can see,
I'm hopelessly in love.

00:00:33.840 --> 00:00:38.781 align:middle line:90%


00:00:38.781 --> 00:00:40.530 align:middle line:90%
Why do of people say hopelessly?

00:00:40.530 --> 00:00:43.750 align:middle line:90%
I'm hopeful.

00:00:43.750 --> 00:00:47.400 align:middle line:84%
I could not be more
full of hope and love.

00:00:47.400 --> 00:00:49.420 align:middle line:84%
Who is the object
of my love, you ask?

00:00:49.420 --> 00:00:52.250 align:middle line:90%
The apple of my juice?

00:00:52.250 --> 00:00:54.642 align:middle line:84%
Most people would call
her my babysitter.

00:00:54.642 --> 00:00:58.570 align:middle line:84%
But I call her Lila,
goddess of my dreams.

00:00:58.570 --> 00:01:01.363 align:middle line:84%
She lifts me up when
I'm down, carries me

00:01:01.363 --> 00:01:04.129 align:middle line:84%
when the pressures of
life become too great,

00:01:04.129 --> 00:01:05.665 align:middle line:90%
gives me a push when I need.

00:01:05.665 --> 00:01:07.410 align:middle line:90%
We are soul mates.

00:01:07.410 --> 00:01:08.250 align:middle line:90%
I know it.

00:01:08.250 --> 00:01:09.160 align:middle line:90%
She knows it.

00:01:09.160 --> 00:01:11.510 align:middle line:84%
And soon the world will
know it, because today

00:01:11.510 --> 00:01:14.636 align:middle line:90%
I will profess my love for her.

00:01:14.636 --> 00:01:16.133 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:16.133 --> 00:01:30.120 align:middle line:90%


00:01:30.120 --> 00:01:30.836 align:middle line:90%
There you are.

00:01:30.836 --> 00:01:31.828 align:middle line:90%
Hi, honey.

00:01:31.828 --> 00:01:37.780 align:middle line:90%


00:01:37.780 --> 00:01:38.620 align:middle line:90%
I brought you something.

00:01:38.620 --> 00:01:43.900 align:middle line:90%


00:01:43.900 --> 00:01:48.700 align:middle line:84%
Look, Harry, college
is coming up.

00:01:48.700 --> 00:01:52.350 align:middle line:84%
And, well, I think
you're the best.

00:01:52.350 --> 00:01:54.230 align:middle line:84%
And nothing can
ever change that.

00:01:54.230 --> 00:01:55.930 align:middle line:90%
But I'm going away.

00:01:55.930 --> 00:01:59.400 align:middle line:84%
And I can't be your
babysitter anymore.

00:01:59.400 --> 00:02:00.870 align:middle line:90%
I'm really excited.

00:02:00.870 --> 00:02:03.320 align:middle line:84%
And I want you to be
excited about it too.

00:02:03.320 --> 00:02:06.260 align:middle line:84%
We get do new, fun
things that we wouldn't

00:02:06.260 --> 00:02:08.220 align:middle line:90%
have gotten [INAUDIBLE].

00:02:08.220 --> 00:02:12.420 align:middle line:90%


00:02:12.420 --> 00:02:14.514 align:middle line:84%
But I'll always
remember you, Harry.

00:02:14.514 --> 00:02:21.430 align:middle line:90%


00:02:21.430 --> 00:02:23.406 align:middle line:90%
[WIND BLOWING]

00:02:23.406 --> 00:02:27.852 align:middle line:90%


00:02:27.852 --> 00:02:28.840 align:middle line:90%
[BANG]

00:02:28.840 --> 00:02:56.090 align:middle line:90%


00:02:56.090 --> 00:02:59.380 align:middle line:84%
HARRY (VOICEOVER): For a brief
moment of groggy morning bliss,

00:02:59.380 --> 00:03:00.410 align:middle line:90%
I forget my pain.

00:03:00.410 --> 00:03:04.490 align:middle line:90%


00:03:04.490 --> 00:03:08.472 align:middle line:84%
But with daylight,
sorrow floods my heart,

00:03:08.472 --> 00:03:11.770 align:middle line:90%
and sometimes my diaper.

00:03:11.770 --> 00:03:12.540 align:middle line:90%
Nothing looks familiar.

00:03:12.540 --> 00:03:15.590 align:middle line:90%


00:03:15.590 --> 00:03:18.110 align:middle line:84%
Maybe seeing my reflection
in my favorite storefront

00:03:18.110 --> 00:03:20.402 align:middle line:90%
will remind me I'm alive.

00:03:20.402 --> 00:03:23.378 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:03:23.378 --> 00:03:56.120 align:middle line:90%


00:03:56.120 --> 00:03:57.510 align:middle line:90%
LILA: Hi, this is Lila.

00:03:57.510 --> 00:03:59.060 align:middle line:84%
I can't come to the
phone right now.

00:03:59.060 --> 00:04:00.654 align:middle line:84%
So leave a message and
I'll call you back.

00:04:00.654 --> 00:04:01.353 align:middle line:90%
[BEEP]

00:04:01.353 --> 00:04:02.260 align:middle line:90%


00:04:02.260 --> 00:04:03.150 align:middle line:90%
LILA: Hey, it's Lila.

00:04:03.150 --> 00:04:05.240 align:middle line:84%
I've only got this phone
for a few more days.

00:04:05.240 --> 00:04:06.330 align:middle line:90%
So leave a message.

00:04:06.330 --> 00:04:08.340 align:middle line:84%
I will call you back
with my new area code.

00:04:08.340 --> 00:04:10.250 align:middle line:84%
[BEEP]
WOMAN: We're sorry.

00:04:10.250 --> 00:04:13.500 align:middle line:84%
The number you have reached
has been disconnected

00:04:13.500 --> 00:04:14.702 align:middle line:90%
or is no longer in service.

00:04:14.702 --> 00:04:16.827 align:middle line:90%


00:04:16.827 --> 00:04:18.560 align:middle line:84%
HARRY (VOICEOVER): I'm not
the first heartbroken New

00:04:18.560 --> 00:04:19.839 align:middle line:90%
Yorker to turn to the bottle.

00:04:19.839 --> 00:04:22.192 align:middle line:90%
But even that's no comfort.

00:04:22.192 --> 00:04:23.534 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:23.534 --> 00:04:29.204 align:middle line:90%


00:04:29.204 --> 00:04:31.070 align:middle line:84%
HARRY (VOICEOVER): Why are
black and white movie so sad?

00:04:31.070 --> 00:04:38.970 align:middle line:90%


00:04:38.970 --> 00:04:43.042 align:middle line:84%
Why does the girl
always leave in the end?

00:04:43.042 --> 00:04:44.521 align:middle line:90%
[THUNDER]

00:04:44.521 --> 00:04:48.465 align:middle line:90%


00:04:48.465 --> 00:04:50.437 align:middle line:90%
[RAIN FALLING]

00:04:50.437 --> 00:05:03.750 align:middle line:90%


00:05:03.750 --> 00:05:07.300 align:middle line:84%
HARRY (VOICEOVER): It's spraying
everywhere but in my heart.

00:05:07.300 --> 00:05:09.430 align:middle line:90%
I will never love again.

00:05:09.430 --> 00:05:13.200 align:middle line:84%
I'm still an empty shell, just
like that empty storefront--

00:05:13.200 --> 00:05:14.590 align:middle line:90%
wait a minute.

00:05:14.590 --> 00:05:16.349 align:middle line:90%
What's this?

00:05:16.349 --> 00:05:18.345 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:18.345 --> 00:07:44.053 align:middle line:90%


00:07:44.053 --> 00:07:46.090 align:middle line:90%
HARRY (VOICEOVER): I love Zoey.

00:07:46.090 --> 00:07:51.080 align:middle line:84%
And, yet, sometimes
I feel anxious.

00:07:51.080 --> 00:07:53.860 align:middle line:84%
Can I handle the responsibility
of taking care of not just

00:07:53.860 --> 00:07:57.560 align:middle line:90%
myself, but her too?

00:07:57.560 --> 00:07:59.760 align:middle line:90%
Did we commit too quickly?

00:07:59.760 --> 00:08:04.551 align:middle line:84%
Are we, as some have
whispered, too young?

00:08:04.551 --> 00:08:06.539 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:08:06.539 --> 00:09:06.680 align:middle line:90%


00:09:06.680 --> 00:09:10.840 align:middle line:84%
HARRY (VOICEOVER): I
promised myself never again.

00:09:10.840 --> 00:09:13.620 align:middle line:84%
But there are things
Zoey can't do for me,

00:09:13.620 --> 00:09:15.035 align:middle line:90%
like reach the top shelf.

00:09:15.035 --> 00:09:18.010 align:middle line:90%


00:09:18.010 --> 00:09:21.440 align:middle line:90%
I wonder what she'll be like.

00:09:21.440 --> 00:09:24.780 align:middle line:84%
Will she make me feel
the way I used to feel?

00:09:24.780 --> 00:09:26.080 align:middle line:90%
Will she stay?

00:09:26.080 --> 00:09:28.980 align:middle line:90%


00:09:28.980 --> 00:09:31.860 align:middle line:84%
Will I finally sleep in
this city that never sleeps,

00:09:31.860 --> 00:09:33.526 align:middle line:90%
feeling safe and secure?

00:09:33.526 --> 00:09:35.430 align:middle line:90%
[BUZZING]

00:09:35.430 --> 00:09:41.150 align:middle line:90%


00:09:41.150 --> 00:09:44.870 align:middle line:84%
HARRY (VOICEOVER):
And, most importantly,

00:09:44.870 --> 00:09:45.760 align:middle line:90%
will Zoey like her?

00:09:45.760 --> 00:09:51.450 align:middle line:90%


00:09:51.450 --> 00:09:55.300 align:middle line:84%
Because I now know what I
wish I'd known all along.

00:09:55.300 --> 00:09:56.650 align:middle line:84%
You can't fall for
your babysitter.

00:09:56.650 --> 00:10:02.914 align:middle line:90%


00:10:02.914 --> 00:10:04.390 align:middle line:90%
They take care of you.

00:10:04.390 --> 00:10:07.150 align:middle line:84%
But they come and
go, like buses.

00:10:07.150 --> 00:10:11.110 align:middle line:90%


00:10:11.110 --> 00:10:17.685 align:middle line:84%
Only true love lasts a
lifetime, at least ours has.

00:10:17.685 --> 00:10:19.625 align:middle line:90%
But what do we know?

00:10:19.625 --> 00:10:23.810 align:middle line:84%
We're new to this world.
We're babies.

00:10:23.810 --> 00:10:32.810 align:middle line:90%


00:10:32.810 --> 00:10:35.860 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:10:35.860 --> 00:11:27.467 align:middle line:90%